    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-30T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-30T23:00:00-05:00" n="560"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d560">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9804: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tsingtao</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sokobin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tsingtao</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-31T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 31, 1937—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 31—1:50
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Japanese Consul General has just informed me that he and his entire staff will
                    withdraw by the 5th of September. Japanese Government has also ordered complete
                    evacuation at once of all remaining Japanese nationals. Japanese Consul General
                    even asked that I ask Yamamoto, our Japanese clerk, to return to Japan. Reason
                    given is reiterated desire to avoid any possible incident which might aggravate
                    the situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sokobin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
